All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Apples
Class representing apples to collect in a game.
Collisions
This class provides static methods for handling collisions in a game.
Constants
The Constants class is used to store all necessary constants for the game.
Controller
The Controller class is used to manage the interactions between the user and the game.
EMapType
Enumeration representing the different types of entities in a game map.
Enemy
The Enemy class represents an enemy in a game.
Flag
This class represents a flag in the game, which is a subclass of ImageView in JavaFX.
Game
Main game class managing game logic, animations, and event handling.
Jeu
The Jeu class extends the Application class from the JavaFX library.
MapEntity
This class represents a map entity which is a subclass of ImageView.
Player
This class represents a player in the game.
Pnj
Class representing a Non-Player Character (NPC) in a game.
TileMaps
This class provides methods to initialize the game map.
